#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:5
msgid "Ubuntu packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:9
msgid ""
"`Scrapinghub`_ publishes apt-gettable packages which are generally fresher "
"than those in Ubuntu, and more stable too since they're continuously built "
"from `Github repo`_ (master & stable branches) and so they contain the "
"latest bug fixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:14
msgid "To use the packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:16
msgid "Import the GPG key used to sign Scrapy packages into APT keyring::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:18
msgid ""
"sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 627220E7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:20
msgid ""
"Create `/etc/apt/sources.list.d/scrapy.list` file using the following "
"command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:22
msgid ""
"echo 'deb http://archive.scrapy.org/ubuntu scrapy main' | sudo tee /etc/apt/"
"sources.list.d/scrapy.list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:24
msgid "Update package lists and install the scrapy-|version| package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:28
msgid "sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install scrapy-|version|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:30
msgid "Repeat step 3 if you are trying to upgrade Scrapy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/ubuntu.rst:32
msgid ""
"`python-scrapy` is a different package provided by official debian "
"repositories, it's very outdated and it isn't supported by Scrapy team."
msgstr ""
